Heals:  Nothing better than to come on raids to do the most boring job (healing) and not even get to be appreciated like the clerics!<br>
Buffs: PotG/resists are all they have that gets used.  And PotG is only used on casters<br>
Harmony: not used on raids<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Am I missing something?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Yep, you're missing the fact that the balance problem is on raids, not &quot;who can solo/duel/group the best.&quot;  Everyone can get to 60, not everyone is useful once they're there.  Though personally, I feel useful on our raids.  We could use some minor fixes (preferably slightly increased pet damage to uber mobs), but overall I'm pretty much pleased with my class.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> We're the MASTERS of all 4 elements...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
That could be debated, and I will.  Regardless of what the bloody manual says (VI has a communication problem, the class designers don't talk with the quest designers, whoever writes the manual, etc. very often).  Personally, I view us as the masters of summoning, not the elements.  We're so good at summoning that we can summon elementals to fight for us, even an elemental made of all the elements.  Or we can summon monsters.  We summon blades to strike our enemies, or balls of fire.  We summon shields of fire to protect ourselves/friends.  We summon piles of junk that are sometimes useful <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> ...,how many other classes can say that?? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Well, druids have more right to it than us...<br>
Wind: They ride the wind (Kunark evacs), and can stun/damage their enemies with the wind.<br>
Fire: They can burn their enemies.<br>
Water: They can freeze their enemies, and can stop the rain.<br>
Earth: They can root their enemies, and can cause earthquakes.<br>
Though the masters of nature would be more appropriate for them. <p>~~
