<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Oh yeah, balance again. So first you talk about how ALL classes are balanced, THEN y ou say some classes are useless on raids??? Oh yeah... balance. Very balanced indeed<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
The only places the classes are balanced is in grouping situations.  On raids there is an extreme inbalance between classes, worse for some than others.  There are two parts of this game, or 3 if you count soloing.  The single group hunting for exp, and the raids made of many groups accomplishing a goal other than exp.  The game was originally designed for only the first, however turned into the second and the classes weren't designed for it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Uhhh, no. That cannot be debated. Mages are the masters of SUMMONING AND ELEMENTS.... or at least we're supposed to be the master of elements. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
According to Verant:<br>
<br>
M A G I C I A N<br>
Magicians are the summoners of the arcane world, with the power to call forth everything from a loaf of bread to a huge fire elemental to fight for them. While not as adept at offensive spells as wizards, magicians still wield considerable power in this area. Magicians, like enchanters, are found among the more intelligent races and worship a variety of deities.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/guidebook/classes.jsp">everquest.station.sony.co...lasses.jsp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
And when you start a mage it says that they can summon exrta-planar beings to fight for them (or a variation on that depending on the race).  The only exception is the DE mage, which doesn't talk about the class at all.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Again, thx so much for describing what spells we get. I, haing played my mage for months, don't know what spells we get. Thx so much. I print this and keep it with me always.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
